      <h1 class='title'>Network Rail</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 15 September 2004 vol 424 c152WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_152ws' title='Col. 152WS &mdash; HC Deb 15 September 2004 vol 424 c152WS' name='column_152ws' href='#column_152ws' rel='bookmark'>152WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040915_CWS_5'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-alistair-darling' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040915_CWS_5' title='Link to this speech by Mr Alistair Darling' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-alistair-darling" title="Mr Alistair Darling">The Secretary of State for Transport (Mr. Alistair Darling)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">Network Rail plans to launch a Debt Issuance Programme (DIP) later this autumn. This will provide a long term, flexible financing platform for Network Rail. It will allow the company to raise finance at a lower cost than the previously envisaged securitisation. Details of the DIP and the support Government intends to provide for it by means of a financial indemnity are set out in Minutes laid before the House today.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
